  "prompt": "Why can't Barack Obama run for reelection as President in 2016?",
  "response": "Barack Obama could not run for reelection as President in 2016 because of the limitations set by the 22nd Amendment to the U.S. Constitution. The 22nd Amendment, ratified in 1951, states that no person can be elected to the office of the President more than twice. Since Obama was elected and served two full terms from January 20, 2009, to January 20, 2017, he was not eligible to run for the presidency again in 2016 or in any future election.",
